import HashSig.SLHDSA.C13.Concrete

/-!
# C13 known-answer test (keccak256, 32-byte ADRS)

A deterministic C13 reference vector — `(PK.seed, PK.root, signature)` over a fixed 32-byte
message — produced by the SPHINCs- repo reference signer (`script/signer.py c13`, which the
on-chain `SPHINCs-C13Asm.sol` verifier accepts). `main` checks that the pure-Lean C13
`verifyBytes` accepts the honest signature and rejects a tampered message, validating the
keccak256 tweakable-hash recipes, the 32-byte FIPS uncompressed ADRS layout, the LSB-first
digest slicing, the WOTS+C counter packing, and the 3688-byte wire decoder byte-for-byte.

Only verification (~hundreds of hashes) runs in Lean; C13 key generation / signing are ~10⁹
hashes and stay in the external reference signer.
-/


